OL,3,CEducation Minister says resolving
OL,4,Cindustrial action by teachers 'is a
OL,5,Cpriority'
OL,7,F"That is a priority. We need to
OL,8,Fresolve the industrial action, we need
OL,9,Fto resolve the action short of strike
OL,10,Fwhich does have a detrimental impact
OL,11,Fupon schools being able to deliver for
OL,12,Fchildren and young people.
OL,14,F"I want to see the resolution to that
OL,15,Fvery quickly and so I want to get with
OL,16,Ftalking to the unions and then we get
OL,17,Finto those negotiations, and then we
OL,18,Fcan reach an outcome where they are
OL,19,Fproperly recognised in their terms and
OL,20,Fconditions, and then schools are able
OL,21,Fto get on with teaching children."
